# WSL Builds Project Context

## Documentation audiences

- **`README.md` (repo root):** End users—what the project is, how to install/configure, how to run `./build.sh`, high-level build/component lists. Not maintainer walkthroughs, script wiring, or instructions aimed only at agents.
- **`CONTRIBUTING.md`:** Contributors—lint/test workflow, how to add builds/components, metadata/dispatch (`conf.sh`, `install.sh`, `src/install-dispatch.sh`). Canonical prose for that lives in **Contributing builds / components**.
- **`.cursor/rules/`:** Operational context for the assistant—invariants (e.g. supported entrypoint is `build.sh`; `install.sh` is not meant to be executed standalone), bash conventions, where tests live. Keep rules short; point to `CONTRIBUTING.md` for full explanations.

## Project behaviour

- This repository is a simple WSL2 build system made from Bash scripts. Bash **function** names use **camelCase** (no `snake_case`).
- It is not a package manager or a framework; keep changes small, explicit, and easy to inspect.
- Builds are stacked by running `./build.sh <build-dir> <component>[,<component>...] [additionalargs]... [--force]`.
- Each build directory contains a `conf.sh` (calls `registerBuildMetadata` in `src/build-metadata.sh`), an `install.sh` (sources `src/install-dispatch.sh` only), and optional `install_<component>.sh` files. Shared dispatch logic runs at top level in `install-dispatch.sh` when `build.sh` sources `install.sh`.
- Components should install/configure one focused thing and fit the existing local patterns.
- Prefer existing helpers in `src/` over adding new mechanisms.
- Update **`README.md`** when adding or changing **user-visible** build behaviour (new components users select, args they pass, or build directory purpose). Do **not** put implementation or agent-only notes in the root README—use **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** or rely on Cursor rules.
- After changes that materially affect **contributor workflow**, **test/lint mechanics**, **scaffolding/component patterns**, or **invariants agents rely on**, check whether **`CONTRIBUTING.md`**, **`.cursor/rules/`**, and **`.cursor/skills/`** still match reality; refresh **only where** text would mislead—skip this for trivial typo-only edits or narrowly local fixes that do not change behaviour or conventions.
- Before non-trivial answers or edits, skim `README.md` and `CONTRIBUTING.md` at the repo root, plus the relevant `<build-dir>/README.md` if a specific build is involved.
- **[`bats-core`](https://github.com/bats-core/bats-core)** tests in **`test/docker/*.bats`** run **only inside Docker**: the test image **copies the repo at build time** (no host bind mount); use **`test/run-tests.sh`** locally (lint + image build + run). Before changing `build.sh`, `src/install-dispatch.sh`, helpers, or Bats tests, skim **Testing** in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
